(A project funded by Zhejiang Cultural Art Development Foundation)

2
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:33,640
(Directed by Liu Xue Song)

3
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:37,159
(Episode 35)

4
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:41,840
Mom.

5
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:45,040
Why did you suddenly side with me just now?

6
00:01:45,719 --> 00:01:47,719
It caught me off guard.

7
00:01:49,439 --> 00:01:51,519
You reminded me of my old self.

8
00:01:52,079 --> 00:01:53,519
When I divorced your dad,

9
00:01:53,519 --> 00:01:55,359
everyone was against it.

10
00:01:55,799 --> 00:01:57,400
They said if I got divorced when I was almost 40,

11
00:01:57,519 --> 00:01:58,560
I wouldn't be able to find someone...

12
00:01:58,560 --> 00:02:00,560
who treats me as well as your dad does.

13
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:02,439
But I did it anyway.

14
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:07,239
No one else can understand the life that we want.

15
00:02:07,719 --> 00:02:10,090
We don't need everyone to understand us either.

16
00:02:10,319 --> 00:02:11,560
Yes, that's right.

17
00:02:14,879 --> 00:02:17,000
You're very independent.

18
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:20,280
Actually, independence is developed from hardships.

19
00:02:21,159 --> 00:02:22,400
I'm so ashamed.

20
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,810
I have no idea what you've been through all these years.

21
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,199
But...

22
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,560
compared to the last time you went through a breakup,

23
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:33,120
it's obvious that you've matured.

24
00:02:34,719 --> 00:02:36,159
As parents,

25
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:40,000
we just want our children to be safe...

26
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,280
and have a smooth life.

27
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:45,599
But you weren't meant to live a normal life.

28
00:02:46,319 --> 00:02:47,919
I won't be so stubborn anymore.

29
00:02:50,199 --> 00:02:52,400
You still can't let go of Hou Jue, right?

30
00:02:54,039 --> 00:02:55,280
No.

31
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:57,719
Why are you dragging him into everything?

32
00:03:01,639 --> 00:03:03,520
You can't stop fate from pulling you two together.

33
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:04,879
I think...

34
00:03:05,159 --> 00:03:06,759
we should just let things go with the flow.

35
00:03:35,599 --> 00:03:37,319
You're off. Why aren't you going home?

36
00:03:38,039 --> 00:03:39,400
I'm nervous.

37
00:03:39,639 --> 00:03:41,120
I know you're nervous too.

38
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:43,240
Let's be nervous together for a bit.

39
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:45,199
We're going to war tomorrow.

40
00:03:45,199 --> 00:03:47,680
Every single cell in my body...

41
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:49,439
is excited right now.

42
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:51,800
Do you think we can win?

43
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,919
My dad told me...

44
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:59,240
to never be too confident that you'll win.

45
00:04:00,719 --> 00:04:01,759
Shi Yi told me...

46
00:04:01,759 --> 00:04:04,039
that when they compete in a match,

47
00:04:04,479 --> 00:04:06,599
they never think about whether they'll win or lose.

48
00:04:06,599 --> 00:04:07,840
Do you know what's on their mind?

49
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:09,759
They just want to use every single move...

50
00:04:09,759 --> 00:04:11,879
that they've done in training.

51
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,080
That's enough.

52
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,560
That's how we are right now.

53
00:04:15,439 --> 00:04:16,560
That makes sense.

54
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,279
We'll just think of it as going to an exam...

55
00:04:19,279 --> 00:04:21,480
to test the fruits of our labor.

56
00:04:22,319 --> 00:04:25,279
I feel like going on stage...

57
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:27,120
already counts as winning.

58
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,800
But...

59
00:04:32,170 --> 00:04:34,279
my cervical vertebra is telling me...

60
00:04:34,439 --> 00:04:36,959
that a miracle will happen.

61
00:04:38,050 --> 00:04:39,610
Your cervical vertebra...

62
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:41,800
seems reliable.

63
00:04:46,050 --> 00:04:49,519
How do you think things are at your dad's company now?

64
00:04:50,439 --> 00:04:54,199
My dad loves challenges.

65
00:04:54,199 --> 00:04:55,560
He...

66
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:59,639
is probably nervously scolding people right now.

67
00:05:01,519 --> 00:05:02,639
I can imagine.

68
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:08,839
This has been revised many times.

69
00:05:08,959 --> 00:05:10,610
Why are there still mistakes with the annotations?

70
00:05:13,170 --> 00:05:14,399
I'm sorry, Mr. Hou.

71
00:05:15,050 --> 00:05:17,000
You've all been working here for nothing, right?

72
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,759
If the client sees such a rookie mistake,

73
00:05:19,759 --> 00:05:21,839
I'm not the one who'll be embarrassed.

74
00:05:22,959 --> 00:05:24,480
You're all useless!

75
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:25,480
Ma Yong!

76
00:05:34,399 --> 00:05:35,399
Hurry up and fix it.

77
00:05:35,399 --> 00:05:36,959
- Yes. - Okay.

78
00:06:08,759 --> 00:06:09,800
Hello.

79
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:13,079
I'll be giving you a presentation on our proposal now.

80
00:06:13,519 --> 00:06:14,519
For this project,

81
00:06:14,519 --> 00:06:16,399
the heart of our design...

82
00:06:16,399 --> 00:06:18,800
is a structure without compromising the aesthetics.

83
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:23,199
World-renowned architect I. M. Pei once said that...

84
00:06:23,519 --> 00:06:27,319
architecture is a form of social art.

85
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:32,040
Daylighting will also allow a better view of the sea.

86
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,319
Thank you.

87
00:06:33,319 --> 00:06:35,240
That's my presentation. Thank you.

88
00:06:38,959 --> 00:06:40,480
Thank you for your proposal.

89
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,399
Please rest in the VIP room first.

90
00:06:43,399 --> 00:06:44,959
Let us invite the next company in.

91
00:06:58,879 --> 00:07:00,800
Your presentation was really good just now.

92
00:07:01,279 --> 00:07:02,279
Okay.

93
00:07:02,639 --> 00:07:05,680
Mr. Hou, please rest here for a while.

94
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:08,000
Once we have the results, we'll notify you immediately.

95
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:09,759
I'll get going then.

96
00:07:09,759 --> 00:07:11,560
Great King Company's presentation will begin shortly.

97
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:12,560
Okay.

98
00:07:13,759 --> 00:07:15,000
Hold on.

99
00:07:15,439 --> 00:07:16,839
Great King Company?

100
00:07:17,439 --> 00:07:18,439
From what I know,

101
00:07:18,439 --> 00:07:20,759
Great King Company doesn't know how to design.

102
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:23,160
They hired an external design team.

103
00:07:23,279 --> 00:07:24,639
They're called Hedgehog Factory.

104
00:07:27,959 --> 00:07:29,600
Okay, rest here for a bit.

105
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,399
- Okay. I'll head over there now. - Thank you.

106
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,920
Hedgehog Factory?

107
00:07:34,199 --> 00:07:35,319
I've never heard of them.

108
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,680
Hedgehog Factory...

109
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,920
Okay, let's take a break.

110
00:07:42,959 --> 00:07:44,879
Hedgehog Factory...

111
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,480
Mr. Hou.

112
00:08:59,639 --> 00:09:01,240
The bidding is over.

113
00:09:01,450 --> 00:09:05,279
The bidding is just a formality anyway.

114
00:09:06,559 --> 00:09:07,679
It's like this.

115
00:09:07,679 --> 00:09:09,159
We regret to inform you...

116
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:11,879
that Great King Company has won this project.

117
00:09:11,879 --> 00:09:13,120
What do you mean?

118
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:15,090
- You won the bid. - We won the bid?

119
00:09:21,279 --> 00:09:24,639
Your proposal was extremely well-prepared,

120
00:09:24,639 --> 00:09:26,879
but Great King's proposal is much more interesting.

121
00:09:26,879 --> 00:09:28,759
Moreover, the vote was unanimous.

122
00:09:28,879 --> 00:09:30,120
I'm extremely sorry.

123
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,330
Are they the hedgehogs you were talking about?

124
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:38,159
Yes, it's that group of young people.

125
00:09:40,879 --> 00:09:44,480
- We have to have a feast! - Let's arrange it.

126
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,720
Give us a pay raise.

127
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:51,210
- Let's go! - Let's celebrate.

128
00:10:19,639 --> 00:10:22,600
(Liao Fang)

129
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:57,960
Xiao Wang.

130
00:10:59,399 --> 00:11:01,679
- Drive a little faster. - Okay.

131
00:11:29,919 --> 00:11:31,080
Hello.

132
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:33,799
Okay, go ahead.

133
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:37,480
Okay, I'll ask him for you.

134
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:39,399
Okay. All right.

135
00:11:40,159 --> 00:11:41,159
All right.

136
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:44,159
Mr. Hou, Ms. Liao wants to know when you're going to the office.

137
00:11:44,159 --> 00:11:45,320
She says it's urgent.

138
00:11:48,159 --> 00:11:49,960
What's the matter with these people?

139
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:53,360
Do they have to wait for me to do everything?

140
00:11:53,799 --> 00:11:55,240
They won't even let me breathe.

141
00:12:00,759 --> 00:12:02,559
Mr. Hou, are you all right?

142
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:08,080
You're all hoping something will happen to me, aren't you?

143
00:12:10,399 --> 00:12:12,039
I'm not your clown.

144
00:12:12,799 --> 00:12:13,799
Go.

145
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:15,480
Go!

146
00:13:06,519 --> 00:13:07,639
Mr. Hou.

147
00:13:08,279 --> 00:13:10,639
Mr. Hou. Here, have some water.

148
00:13:10,639 --> 00:13:11,879
Mr. Hou.

149
00:13:37,039 --> 00:13:38,159
Is there anything else?

150
00:13:38,799 --> 00:13:41,519
Mr. Hou, after this month,

151
00:13:42,159 --> 00:13:43,559
I have a family emergency.

152
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:45,399
I have to go home tomorrow.

153
00:13:47,519 --> 00:13:48,639
Why?

154
00:13:49,279 --> 00:13:51,000
My son called me and said...

155
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:52,759
that his wife is about to give birth.

156
00:13:58,639 --> 00:14:00,799
You're telling me you're leaving in such a hurry.

157
00:14:01,519 --> 00:14:02,639
Can you give it a few days?

158
00:14:02,639 --> 00:14:06,120
Can you wait until I've found a new housekeeper?

159
00:14:06,519 --> 00:14:07,879
Actually, no one is home.

160
00:14:07,879 --> 00:14:09,120
What if I forfeit this month's pay?

161
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:10,840
Does it look like I can't afford your salary?

162
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:12,279
I'll pay your entire salary for this month.

163
00:14:12,279 --> 00:14:13,519
Leave now.

164
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:14,720
Go!

165
00:14:15,799 --> 00:14:18,200
You can all leave! Scram, all of you!

166
00:16:39,879 --> 00:16:41,120
Hello, this is 120.

167
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:43,679
Is it the ambulance?

168
00:16:45,399 --> 00:16:46,639
I...

169
00:16:46,639 --> 00:16:48,960
I'm dying.

170
00:16:49,399 --> 00:16:52,960
Help me.

171
00:17:15,559 --> 00:17:16,559
What happened to my dad?

172
00:17:16,559 --> 00:17:17,559
Dad.

173
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,920
Your dad is stable for now.

174
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,410
Don't disturb the patient.

175
00:17:23,410 --> 00:17:25,319
Let's talk outside. Come on.

176
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:37,960
Your dad had a heart attack due to high blood pressure,

177
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:39,079
leading to palpitations.

178
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:42,279
The patient must be careful to regulate his emotions...

179
00:17:42,839 --> 00:17:44,240
and stay positive.

180
00:17:44,359 --> 00:17:48,279
However, your dad had a prior cerebral infarction.

181
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:50,920
He has atherosclerosis.

182
00:17:52,279 --> 00:17:54,119
He also has high blood pressure and high cholesterol levels.

183
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:56,799
After doing an electrocardiogram,

184
00:17:56,799 --> 00:17:58,319
we saw that he may even have coronary heart disease.

185
00:17:58,319 --> 00:18:00,119
Why has his health become like this?

186
00:18:00,410 --> 00:18:01,839
When did he get all these illnesses?

187
00:18:02,519 --> 00:18:05,480
Your dad has already been seeing me for five years.

188
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:07,519
He has been maintaining his health with medicine.

189
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:08,799
In the future,

190
00:18:08,799 --> 00:18:10,240
don't let your dad do any work...

191
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:11,759
that will bring him a lot of stress.

192
00:18:12,359 --> 00:18:13,759
He needs to rest.

193
00:18:14,170 --> 00:18:16,559
Yes. I've never seen him take a break all these years.

194
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:19,519
He has to be careful after he is discharged.

195
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,720
You must bring your dad for regular checkups.

196
00:18:21,839 --> 00:18:23,650
Don't let him come by himself.

197
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:25,240
As his son,

198
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:26,799
you have to personally accompany him here.

199
00:18:26,799 --> 00:18:27,960
- Okay. - All right.

200
00:18:28,079 --> 00:18:29,319
Thank you, doctor.

201
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:30,799
Okay.

202
00:18:59,839 --> 00:19:01,359
Your responsiveness has slowed down.

203
00:19:01,359 --> 00:19:02,559
What are you thinking about?

204
00:19:03,079 --> 00:19:04,200
Nothing.

205
00:19:05,279 --> 00:19:08,559
Being in love sure makes a difference.

206
00:19:09,890 --> 00:19:11,650
Even your skin looks better.

207
00:19:12,519 --> 00:19:14,000
Don't tease me.

208
00:19:15,240 --> 00:19:16,759
What's the saying?

209
00:19:17,039 --> 00:19:18,410
As long as you're with someone you like,

210
00:19:18,410 --> 00:19:19,839
you're happy even just eating bran.

211
00:19:19,839 --> 00:19:21,039
But if you're with someone you don't like,

212
00:19:21,039 --> 00:19:23,319
even the most luxurious foods taste bland.

213
00:19:24,650 --> 00:19:25,680
That's right.

214
00:19:25,839 --> 00:19:27,319
Now that I'm with you,

215
00:19:27,559 --> 00:19:29,960
even drinking water is like drinking honey, okay?

216
00:19:30,119 --> 00:19:31,799
How sweet.

217
00:19:41,839 --> 00:19:44,170
(Zhou Quan)

218
00:19:45,079 --> 00:19:46,279
Hello.

219
00:19:46,279 --> 00:19:49,200
Hello, it's me. Hou Zhi Rong is sick.

220
00:19:49,410 --> 00:19:50,650
But he's okay now.

221
00:19:50,759 --> 00:19:52,960
He has been moved from the ER to a hospital room.

222
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:56,720
Hou Jue has been at the hospital...

223
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:58,279
ever since getting the call.

224
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:00,799
I don't think he's in good condition right now.

225
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:03,839
If you have time,

226
00:20:04,279 --> 00:20:05,480
come over.

227
00:20:05,480 --> 00:20:08,200
- He could use some encouragement. - Okay, I got it. Thank you.

228
00:20:11,170 --> 00:20:12,410
What's wrong?

229
00:20:12,599 --> 00:20:13,890
Hou Zhi Rong is in the hospital.

230
00:20:14,650 --> 00:20:15,920
He's in the hospital?

231
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:17,680
So what's his situation now?

232
00:20:18,519 --> 00:20:20,920
They moved him to a regular room.

233
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:22,240
He should be fine now.

234
00:20:22,839 --> 00:20:23,920
I'm going to go now. I'll go and take a look.

235
00:20:23,920 --> 00:20:25,170
I'll go with you.

236
00:20:25,519 --> 00:20:26,890
Don't you have class later?

237
00:20:29,759 --> 00:20:31,000
Take my car.

238
00:20:33,170 --> 00:20:34,279
Take this water.

239
00:20:34,440 --> 00:20:35,680
I'm leaving.

240
00:20:56,440 --> 00:20:58,079
The index levels haven't changed much.

241
00:20:58,079 --> 00:20:59,359
We have to observe him carefully.

242
00:21:03,279 --> 00:21:04,410
Why are you here?

243
00:21:06,039 --> 00:21:07,359
Zhou Quan called me,

244
00:21:07,519 --> 00:21:08,759
so I came to take a look.

245
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:10,480
How's Mr. Hou?

246
00:21:11,680 --> 00:21:12,920
He hasn't woken up yet.

247
00:21:13,799 --> 00:21:15,119
What did the doctor say?

248
00:21:15,839 --> 00:21:17,200
He has a bunch of illnesses.

249
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:18,480
It's a result of fatigue.

250
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,170
Don't worry. He'll be okay.

251
00:21:38,559 --> 00:21:41,079
It's my fault. I never paid attention to his health.

252
00:21:41,359 --> 00:21:42,720
He was busy with the bid every day.

253
00:21:42,720 --> 00:21:44,920
This probably also happened because he was too upset...

254
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:46,200
about losing the bid.

255
00:21:46,650 --> 00:21:48,519
Otherwise, he wouldn't have collapsed so quickly.

256
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,400
You can't be blamed.

257
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:53,039
I'm sure he didn't want you to know.

258
00:21:55,720 --> 00:21:58,319
Mr. Hou is too prideful and eager to be good at everything.

259
00:21:58,480 --> 00:22:00,640
Why does he need to compete with his own son?

260
00:22:00,880 --> 00:22:02,960
Who else can he tell about his health problems?

261
00:22:03,240 --> 00:22:05,279
I should've known about this.

262
00:22:05,839 --> 00:22:07,440
When he fainted in the company last time,

263
00:22:07,920 --> 00:22:09,880
I should have paid more attention and asked him more questions.

264
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:11,400
I accompanied him to the hospital...

265
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:13,279
and he started lecturing me the moment we sat down.

266
00:22:13,599 --> 00:22:14,960
I can't stand that.

267
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:17,519
It's also my fault.

268
00:22:18,599 --> 00:22:20,319
I kept playing around.

269
00:22:20,319 --> 00:22:21,559
All I did was make him mad.

270
00:22:22,240 --> 00:22:23,519
I couldn't do anything right.

271
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,240
Stop blaming yourself.

272
00:22:27,119 --> 00:22:29,440
At least you won the bid.

273
00:22:30,319 --> 00:22:31,400
As for Mr. Hou,

274
00:22:32,079 --> 00:22:33,720
he'll be gratified...

275
00:22:34,440 --> 00:22:35,759
that he lost to his son.

276
00:22:40,039 --> 00:22:42,000
I really wanted to win this bid.

277
00:22:43,039 --> 00:22:45,160
But I want my family's company to do well even more.

278
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:47,559
Who doesn't want to help their own family's company do well?

279
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:51,480
But my dad is too strong.

280
00:22:56,720 --> 00:22:58,480
If you really stayed in the company,

281
00:22:58,480 --> 00:23:00,119
it may not have necessarily been a good thing.

282
00:23:01,039 --> 00:23:02,119
Without experiencing all this,

283
00:23:02,279 --> 00:23:03,279
I don't think...

284
00:23:03,279 --> 00:23:05,000
you would be able to understand your dad like this today.

285
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:06,640
Who knows?

286
00:23:09,119 --> 00:23:11,240
All right, don't think too much.

287
00:23:12,039 --> 00:23:13,759
It's not too late to be nicer to him from now on.

288
00:23:14,039 --> 00:23:16,079
If I'm not nice to him, who will?

289
00:23:16,799 --> 00:23:17,920
I'm the only one left.

290
00:23:24,039 --> 00:23:25,160
Hello.

291
00:23:26,759 --> 00:23:28,000
Slow down.

292
00:23:29,759 --> 00:23:31,000
What's wrong?

293
00:23:34,119 --> 00:23:35,240
I'm coming.

294
00:23:36,759 --> 00:23:38,160
What's wrong? What happened?

295
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:40,640
Since my dad has collapsed,

296
00:23:40,880 --> 00:23:41,920
